  "instructions": [
    "Cook yellow masarepa pasta in salted water until al dente (10-12 mins).",
    "While pasta cooks, toast dates in a dry pan over medium heat for 2 minutes to enhance sweetness.",
    "In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-low, add minced garlic and cumin; sauté for 1 minute.",
    "Add toasted dates, lemon juice, red pepper flakes, and 1 cup water; simmer for 5 minutes until sauce thickens.",
    "Add cooked pasta to the sauce, toss gently to coat, and stir in chopped parsley.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste; serve immediately."
